Source: newlib
Section: devel
Priority: extra
Maintainer: Arthur Loiret <aloiret@debian.org>
Uploaders: Matthias Klose <doko@debian.org>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 6), quilt (>= 0.40), texinfo, binutils-spu [powerpc ppc64], gcc-spu [powerpc ppc64]
Build-Depends-Indep:  mingw32
Standards-Version: 3.8.0

Package: libnewlib0
Section: libs
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: newlib C library (runtime)
 Newlib is a C library intended for use on embedded systems. It is a
 conglomeration of several library parts, all under free software
 licenses that make them easily usable on embedded products.
 .
 This package contains the newlib runtime library.

Package: libnewlib-dev
Section: libdevel
Architecture: any
Depends: libnewlib0 (= ${binary:Version}), ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
